The paper proposes a heuristic genetic algorithm for pruning convolutional neural networks (CNNs) based on a multi-objective trade-off among error, computation, and sparsity. This work is related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY) as it deals with optimizing CNNs for efficient computation and accuracy.
